                            <comment id="13697966" author="ignaced" created="Tue, 2 Jul 2013 16:49:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I did try your latest patch, applied on 1.2.5. Looks good, no more exceptions due to the start() calls. Question/remark : Also that implementation to shutdown allows the uncaught exceptions to finish without problems. Should these be blocked instead?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13697980" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 2 Jul 2013 17:00:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure what you mean.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13698744" author="ignaced" created="Wed, 3 Jul 2013 08:29:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I forgot the fact that the thread is dead when the uncaught exception handling is called and thus was thinking that thread would continue to run until the system.exit would stop all the threads.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
